# <span id="index"></span>Live log

The Live log page shows real-time logs of the IBIS application as they
occur.

An advantage of using the Live log over the regular loging is that
troubleshooting issues is easier. However, the Live log only displays
logs from the moment it runs and does not show past logs (use the
regular logging for that). When opening the Live log, it will
automatically start showing the INFO, WARNING and ERROR log levels.

To view the Live log: click on the "All pages" menu item. When the
sidepanel opens click on "Live log" (Only accesible by administrators)

#### Main page

The main page shows logs in real-time as they occur. Here you can:

-   Start / stop the Live log
-   Look for a log that contains a specific keyword (using the filter
    field)
-   Specify which log levels need to be displayed
-   Clear the Live log
-   Enable / Disable the autoscroll

#### Start / stop the Live log

When opening the Live Log, it will automatically "Start", showing log
levels as they occur.

-   To stop the Live log from running, press the "Stop" button.
-   To Start the Live log press the "Start" button.

#### Look for a log that contains a specific keyword

-   Make sure that the Live Log has log entries on the page
-   Enter a keyword in the "Contains" search field and press Enter

#### Clear the Live log

When the Live log has run for a while, you can clear the clutter by
pressing the "Clear Live log" button

#### Enable / Disable the autoscroll

By default, the Live log will have autoscroll on

-   To stop it from automatically scrolling: click the (green) arrow
    icon on the right side of the page
-   To enable the autoscroll: click the (red) arrow icon on the right
    side of the page
